I just wanted to point out what appears to be an error in the EHR Data Submission Report.  The Lab Concept Summary section of our most recent report (attached) shows that we do not have concept_id 3019204 (Body position with respect to gravity) mapped.  However, we do have that concept mapped in the Observation table.  We have placed it there because it is listed as being in the Observation domain in the concept table.

description:
Hello,

 

I was going to look at the most recent EHR receipt dates for PMIDs in HealthPro and I noticed that some dates were missing.  For example, with Cooper Green, I wanted to look at PMIDs with the most recent EHR receipt date of 3/31/22, however HealthPro shows 3/18/22, then it jumps to 4/18/22, and finally to the most recent date of 4/25/22. I’ve noticed this with a few other sites in the Southern Network as well. Is the new OMOP version overwriting old upload dates? Thanks for your help!

 

-Matt

 

-- 

Matthew Phillips | Program Director I, Retention Lead 

All of Us Southern Network 

UAB | The University of Alabama at Birmingham 

KAUL 213 | 720 20th Street South | Birmingham, AL 35294-0024

description:
Hi All of Us DRC,

 

I have a PI (principal investigator) interested in breast cancer research.  Her analyst attempted to query the following Concept ID’s.

 

concept_id | concept_code |               concept_name               | vocabulary_id | standard_concept

------------+--------------+------------------------------------------+---------------+------------------

    4030768 | 129715009    | Breast composition                       | SNOMED        | S

    4031228 | 129717001    | Scattered fibroglandular densities       | SNOMED        | S

    4031229 | 129718006    | Heterogeneously dense breast composition | SNOMED        | S

    4031230 | 129719003    | Extremely dense breast composition       | SNOMED        | S

    4032368 | 129716005    | Almost entirely fat breast composition   | SNOMED        | S

 

The analyst only came back with 103 individuals nationwide.   That seems wrong to him because he expects a lot more (thousands). 

 

We need to know which breast-cancer related concepts are truly well-populated in the All of Us system nationwide.  Could you please point us to documentation on which breast-cancer concepts are standard and well-populated at the national All of Us level?

 

IF there is any recommendation on how to query and find breast composition like what’s listed above, please advise.  It will help garner support and trust among the PI’s here.  

 

Oliver Eng

Data Query Analyst

Clinical Research Data Service team (CRDS)

UW Madison School of Medicine and Public Health

1212 Deming Way, Madison, WI 53717

OEng@uwhealth.org | 608.720.6248

We received a question from UCSF asking how EHR Transfer status is calculated.

What is the criteria for EHR Transfer Status = Yes? They say they are seeing ~1100 participants that qualify while they believe only ~600 should be.

I will ask the RDR what info we have for those two ppts.

to.name: All of Us EHR Ops Team

description:
Good morning,

I am with SEEC and we are working with our partners at UM to bring their physical measurement counts up for Refresh 16. Current their height, weight, bp, and hr are all at 73%. It seems that this is due to them enrolling patients who are seen in their Jackson facility. Because of the way their health system works, this would make these participants eligible for patient status=yes, but the UM EHR system only has access to the billing information for these visits while the health records themselves stay locked in the Jackson system. Essentially these are empty placeholder visits in the UM EHR system. We believe the best and most accurate way to resolve this is to change these participants patient status to 'no' and not send the records for these participants. We wanted to see if the DRC agrees with this approach. We appreciate your assistance and feedback with this issue and the sooner we get an answer back to UM the sooner they can resubmit data to SEEC for processing.

Thank you,
Donny Weinbrenner

description:
Hello,

 

I would like to confirm that we have submitted the OMOP tables for Unity Point. Has the system determined success? We usually get a system confirmation within a few hours for our other Google buckets, but the Google bucket for UnityPoint has not been received. Could you look to see if aou824 is paired to UnityPoint and if the results for curation? I am not able to use pull any results on my end.

 

 

In addition, the primary data team is not receiving notifications for submission, which usually occurs a few hours after loading. Could you add me (the data steward for UIC) and Christine Jovanovic (the director of research operations) to the email list notifications for future uploads? The primary Google buckets we would need notifications for are The University of Illinois at Chicago (UIC: aou336), Unity Point (aou824), and Cook County.

 

Thank you,

Christian

 

 

---

Christian Udu, MPH

He/Him

Biomedical Informatics Research Specialist, All of Us

Institute for Minority Health Research

University of Illinois Chicago.

E: cudu@uic.edu | O: 312-413-3568

description:
Hey Michael and Sergio,

 

Happy to meet sometime starting next week! Go ahead and pick a time on our Calendly (https://calendly.com/ehrops/30min?month=2022-09&date=2022-09-12) and be sure to fill out as much information as possible on questions you have for the data steward process.

 

How has the onboarding process gone so far? Have you checked out our articles on ZenDesk? We’ve worked on it, but some users have had issues accessing them. Those are your best bet for FAQs.

If you have a one-off question feel free to send it to our technical group at support@aou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com

 

Looking forward to chatting,

Michael

Do you have any time this week for a meeting with Sergio to discuss the AOU EHR file check?  He has some questions about this part of the Data Steward process

 

If the end of quarter wrap up is still going on we can schedule for later this month, just let me know what works better for you

 

Michael Audet

 

Clinical Quality and Informatics Department

Health Transformation Technical Center

The MITRE Corporation

Mobile: (571) 369-8059 | email: maudet@mitre.org

 

From: Tokarz, Michael <michael.tokarz@vumc.org>
Sent: Wednesday, August 17, 2022 5:02 PM
To: Maldonado, Sergio <sergio.maldonado@cossma.org>; Mike Audet <maudet@mitre.org>
Subject: RE: [EXT] RE: New FQHC Introductions

 

Hey Sergio,

 

Nice to meet you! We are excited to hear about your site joining All of Us. Right now, our EHR Ops team is wrapping up end-of-the-quarter site data submissions – so let’s schedule something for the beginning of September to connect and make introductions.

 

In the meantime, feel free to check out our knowledge articles (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Faou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us&data=05%7C01%7Cmichael.tokarz%40vumc.org%7Cec96066165ef45aa1d3708da9046352f%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637980928467481634%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=KKOeDAvBdpXkyYJftUynM%2FPlkh2z%2BYuf5P9U8ei5QTc%3D&reserved=0) on ZenDesk. Especially data steward registration, making your first submission (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Faou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Fcategories%2F1500001782581-Making-File-Submission&data=05%7C01%7Cmichael.tokarz%40vumc.org%7Cec96066165ef45aa1d3708da9046352f%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637980928467481634%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=wCD6YP74MksHXW3JKzBnjo%2BfBziMt%2Fkji6NSjXI8%2FV0%3D&reserved=0) , and OMOP CDM (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Faou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com%2Fhc%2Fen-us%2Farticles%2F1500012461401-OMOP-CDM-Overview-v5-3-1-&data=05%7C01%7Cmichael.tokarz%40vumc.org%7Cec96066165ef45aa1d3708da9046352f%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637980928467481634%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=p92c4LfgjBOX%2FVBuvihNZa7aSNPiBJrvE7ksy1mrWf4%3D&reserved=0) .

Michael Tokarz

Rob

description:
BSWH is working on new queries for our EHR data pull. There are areas we'd like to improve, specifically, data quality (e.g., height and weight; condition_occurrence concepts) and participant matching.

As work progresses on the new queries, I'd like to propose that we prioritize participant matching (to boost our DTR-C rate) and improve data quality for required fields. This means that for 1 or 2 quarters we may not include all the optional fields we were sending previously.

In the long run, we do intend on sending all optional fields for which we have data. This proposal is really just about how I prioritize the time I spend coding the new queries.

Please let me know what you think.

Hi DRC All of Us support,

 

I recently discovered that “University of Wisconsin, Madison” is responsible for data transfer rates on “Swedish American Regional Center, UW Health” who is also in the Wisconsin Consortium.

 

For “Swedish American Regional Center, UW Health” I see we are sending 90 Participants with EHR data for Transfer Rate A.  But why is the denominator for Transfer Rate C a Big Zero?  The circle is greyed out.

 

1. Is it the Patient Status (YES) causing the denominator to drop to 0?

2. Is it the In Person Visit (YES) causing the denominator to drop to 0?

3. More generally, is there a specific Health Pro field called “In Person Visit”?    I’m having trouble finding something called “In Person Visit” in my Health Pro work queue data that my AoU enrollment staff download for me.

 

   

 

Oliver Eng

description:
Hi Brian, after circling internally we were able to clarify the fields below, however I’ve added the EHR ops team to this email chain, so they can verify what they consider to be the best way to determine eligibility.

 

consentForStudyEnrollment = 1   HPRO Field =Primary Consent Status = Consented

 

consentForElectronicHealthRecords = 1   HPRO Field =EHR Consent Status = Consented

 

withdrawalStatus = 0    HPRO Field =Withdrawal Status = Not Withdrawn

 

onsiteIdVerificationTime = NOT NULL | OR | participant provided records via Sync 4 Science (Sync 4 Science is not a value on the WQ or WQ export) I’m not sure IDV is the right field to determine eligibility, @Chun Yee Lau (All of Us EHR Ops Team) can you clarify whether this or the Patient Status field is the right field to determine eligibility? This field in HealthPro is Patient Status: Yes = Yes. This field indicates the participant has an EHR record as a patient at the site.)

 

If participant located in California,  consentForCABoR = 1    HPRO Field= CABoR Consent Status = Consented

 

For your convenience, I believe this sort of question would be best directed to the EHR Ops team in the future.

 

Thank you!

 

Drew Ericson
Associate IT Business Analyst
Vanderbilt University Medical Center, Data and Research Center

Hi Brian, thanks for your email.

 

I’ve “translated” those criteria into their field name equivalents.

 

The following criteria must be met in order to transfer participant EHR data to the DRC:

consentForStudyEnrollment = 1

AND

consentForElectronicHealthRecords = 1

AND

withdrawalStatus = 0

AND

onsiteIdVerificationTime = NOT NULL | OR | participant provided records via Sync 4 Science (Sync 4 Science is not a value on the WQ or WQ export)

AND

If participant located in California,  consentForCABoR = 1

Hi –

 

I’ve been looking around ZenDesk for a bit now and haven’t come up with a definitive algorithm for determining if a participant is eligible for data transfer.

 

The closest I’ve come is this document:

https://aou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com/hc/en-us/articles/1500012461741-Criteria-for-Participant-EHR-Data-Transfer (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Furldefense.com%2Fv3%2F__https%3A%2Fnam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com%2F%3Furl%3Dhttps*3A*2F*2Furldefense.com*2Fv3*2F__https*3A*2Faou-ehr-ops.zendesk.com*2Fhc*2Fen-us*2Farticles*2F1500012461741-Criteria-for-Participant-EHR-Data-Transfer__*3B!!LLK065n_VXAQ!hh9H3iqiMQjTTQK3ghdb8eKmlzIgDZtWmvdWV8xyvbr8uMANYn4_WO51TkX4on8UsT7tM5L2I31O1ydMhfjz*24%26data%3D05*7C01*7Cdrcsupport*40vumc.org*7C5a56f86ad0c04ad2613b08daa7ba0c23*7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab*7C0*7C0*7C638006714756480437*7CUnknown*7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0*3D*7C3000*7C*7C*7C%26sdata%3D92*2Ff23hPsZMmHncWUoMzbG9N3*2BOSML04oEzuanzFU0Y*3D%26reserved%3D0__%3BJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJSUlJQ!!LLK065n_VXAQ!m5vwbr4mgwfIJFhFj89qSnTmOEwi5_GEHSaFzY4Yl3Gou0OsfyL6DXS3kboIpIP9egjAbNz5aKy0qWoBdYP2%24&data=05%7C01%7Cdrcsupport%40vumc.org%7C7af580f464f645d1c73608dab838a099%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C638024850605671444%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&sdata=w881t4uqjLvmhaj0L63IEhx4Ofxzw8FJWYxeKsVBjO8%3D&reserved=0)

 

Unfortunately criteria like “General Consent = Complete” is not well matched to any of the flags in a HealthPro workqueue export.  And we’re using the workqueue downloads to determine eligibility.  (We don’t have API access yet, not sure if it adds an easier way to tell.)

 

Can you point me to a definitive document that spells out eligibility using the flags available in the workqueue export?

 

Thanks much,

Brian

description:
I'm sure this was already stated but in the event that it was not. 

I was able to find in our data the missing concept id's for the missing "Lab Component Inclusion Rate" on the "Measurement Integration" tab. Most of the missing components for the sites seem to be a "branch" off of the Comprehensive Metabolic Panel or CMP. 

This being said I'm not sure how much medical coding that the data people of other groups have had. But knowing that I've had some blockages with this and other sites had these same concepts missing as well I can only assume maybe they are not bringing in these concepts because lack of medical knowledge? 

Anyway, a simple answer to this is to look in the data for CMP test being done and the 14 separate measurements attached to this CMP.  https://www.testing.com/tests/comprehensive-metabolic-panel-cmp/

Hopefully this helps someone. Please let me know if you need additional information and maybe we can address it in our next meeting?

From: San Chu <San.Chu@pbrc.edu>
Sent: Tuesday, November 15, 2022 12:59 PM
To: Cimino, James <jamescimino@uabmc.edu>; DRC Support <drcsupport@vumc.org>
Cc: Ronald Horswell <Ronald.Horswell@pbrc.edu>; Miele, Lucio (lmiele@lsuhsc.edu) <lmiele@lsuhsc.edu>
Subject: EXT MSG All Of Us/ LSU data

 

Dear Dr. Cimino and DRC-EHR team,

(cc’d Dr. Miele & Dr. Horswell)

 

In the past several weeks, we have identified (and are now in the process of resolving) several problems affecting our AoU data submission for the LSU Health Sciences Center.

 

However, we have one remaining issue that will require somewhat more time to resolve:  The LSU Health Sciences Center AoU enrollees largely are patients at one (or both) of two health care provider systems which have been using two different EMRs; namely, the LSU Health Network (which has used Allscripts) and the University Medical Center (UMC) in New Orleans (which uses Epic.) The LSU Health Network is now discontinuing use of Allscripts and is migrating to use of UMC’s Epic instance. Ultimately, this will allow easier and more complete uploads to AoU for those who enroll in AoU via the LSU Health Network. However, during the transition, we may be NOT able to upload EMR-derived data for those who enrolled via the LSU Health Network.

 

This issue does not affect those who enrolled through UMC and, therefore, does not create any problems for the UMC portion of the data upload. But for those who enrolled via the LSU Health Network, our plan is to temporarily change the “Patient Status” values to “NO ACCESS” for the LSU Health Network enrollees during the above-mentioned transition from Allscripts to Epic. Once we are in a position to do, so we will change the “Patient Status” values for those enrollees back to the original values entered into AllScripts back (“YES” or “NO”),

 

This affects our current LSU data upload, and on Tuesday (Nov 15), I only upload the UMC portion of the data.

 

I have had Dr. Miele’s approval for changing the statuses of LSU Health Network participants to NO ACCESS and would like to inform you before doing it on HealthPro by the end of today .

 

 

Thanks,

San Chu

to.name: All of Us EHR Ops Team

description:
Good Morning, 

 

I just wanted to let you all know that I've attempted to send the data export of the notes file where as requested the notes be on newlines.

I followed the guidelines that were located on the EHR Note pilot directive google docs but the note.jsonl didn’t parse when the contents were on newlines.

After two failed attempts I had to upload the note.jsonl file as a “run on” line to make sure we at least meet the 11/30 deadline.

 

I utilized a python script to alter the file to have each instance of a column be on a new line.

I’m sure I’m just not understanding the instructions. Mike T. if you could please assist I would greatly appreciate it. 

 

I’ll be on vacation from 11/18 to 11/25 however, I did bring my computer and will be checking emails periodically.

 

Example of the contents of the file originally sent 11/17/2022-v1 and 11/17/2022-v2:

{

"note_id": "5555555",

"person_id": "5555555",

"note_date": "2016-03-28",

"note_datetime": "2016-03-28 09:52:23",

"note_type_concept_id": "5555555",

"note_class_concept_id": "5555555",

"note_title": "this is a note title",

"note_text": "this is a note text",

"encoding_concept_id": "5555555",

"language_concept_id": "5555555",

"provider_id": "0",

"visit_occurrence_id": "0",

"visit_detail_id": "0",

"note_source_value": "this is a note source value"

}

 

Kasie Sanders

803-476-6978

Cooperative Heath

Good Morning, 

I just wanted to let you all know that I've attempted to send the data export of the notes file where as requested the notes be on newlines. 
I followed the guidelines that were located on the EHR Note pilot directive google docs but the note.jsonl didn’t parse when the contents were on newlines.
After two failed attempts I had to upload the note.jsonl file as a “run on” line to make sure we at least meet the 11/30 deadline.

I utilized a python script to alter the file to have each instance of a column be on a new line. 
I’m sure I’m just not understanding the instructions. Mike T. if you could please assist I would greatly appreciate it.  

I’ll be on vacation from 11/18 to 11/25 however, I did bring my computer and will be checking emails periodically.

description:
Hi DRC,

I wanted to let you know that after reviewing our results.html file from our 2022-11-30-v1 submission, we made a few updates and resubmitted today with 2022-12-02-v1. This corrects all of the Achilles Heel errors except the one about there being 16 drug_concept_id's not in the vocabulary because when I ran the query (see below), I saw that all domain_id in our drug_occurrence table were in the drug domain. If you have any advice, I'd be happy to investigate further.

Could you confirm receipt and that we made it in for the data drop?

Thanks,

Ashley I. Martinez, PharmD, PhD
Clinical Data Analyst
Rush University Alzheimer's Disease Center

      SELECT DISTINCT c.domain_id, COUNT(*) as count
      FROM drug_exposure co
      JOIN athena.concept c ON c.concept_id = co.drug_concept_id
      WHERE co.drug_concept_id <> 0
      GROUP BY domain_id
      ORDER BY count DESC

description:
From: Fox, Brian <befox@health.ucsd.edu>
Sent: Monday, December 12, 2022 12:09 PM
To: DRC Support <drcsupport@vumc.org>
Cc: Post, Kai <k1post@health.ucsd.edu>; Delaney, Kevin <kjdelaney@health.ucsd.edu>
Subject: Extracting visit table

 

Hi –

 

We’re seeing fewer visit_occurrence rows than we expected.  I may be working off of old concept IDs. 

 

Could you verify the following concept ids?  They are highlighted yellow in the SQL below.  Also, if this is already documented in the wiki, could you point me to the article?

 

Thanks!

Brian

 

 

select DISTINCT

    vo.visit_occurrence_id

    ,d.[person_id] 

    --per DRC, Person_id = PMI_ID (remove 'P')

    ,CASE

        -- Emergency Room Visit

        WHEN ve.visit_subtype_concept_id = 600074763 THEN 9203 

        -- Office Visit

        WHEN vo.visit_concept_id = 600074748 THEN 581477                       

        ELSE vo.visit_concept_id

    END AS [visit_concept_id]

    ,CONVERT(varchar, vo.visit_start_date, 23) visit_start_date

    ,CONVERT(varchar(100), [visit_start_datetime], 126) visit_start_datetime

    ,CONVERT(varchar, vo.visit_end_date, 23) visit_end_date

    ,CONVERT(varchar(100), [visit_end_datetime], 126) visit_end_datetime

    ,[visit_type_concept_id]

    , NULL [provider_id]

    , NULL [care_site_id]

    , NULL [visit_source_value]

    , NULL [visit_source_concept_id]

    , NULL [admitting_source_concept_id]                       

    , NULL [admitting_source_value]                    

    , NULL [discharge_to_concept_id]           

    , NULL [discharge_to_source_value]

    , NULL [preceding_visit_occurrence_id]     

into #visit

    from OMOP.dbo.visit_occurrence vo

    join OMOP.dbo.visit_occurrence_extension ve

        on vo.visit_occurrence_id = ve.visit_occurrence_id

    join OMOP.dbo.person p

        on vo.person_id = p.person_id

    join AllOfUs.dbo.DRC_PII_MRN d on p.person_source_value = d.MRN

    where

 

        -- Visit derived from EHR record

        vo.visit_type_concept_id = 44818518

 

        -- Inpatient, Outpatient, Office, Ambulatory

        and vo.visit_concept_id IN (9201, 9202, 581477, 600074748)

 

    -- Electronic, Phone, Pharmacy

    and ve.visit_subtype_concept_id NOT IN (646370699, 600074754, 646370942)

 

    and vo.visit_end_date >= vo.visit_start_date

    and visit_end_datetime >= vo.visit_start_datetime

-- 

 

Brian Fox

Information Systems Analyst

Department of Biomedical Informatics

befox@health.ucsd.edu

Biomedical Research Facility II (BRF2), 5A20

ON CAMPUS: Mondays, Wednesdays, and Thursdays

WORKING REMOTELY:   Tuesdays and Fridays

description:
Hi EHR Ops team!

 

Christine asked DRC Support a question about how a participant who enrolled through their institution but was not a patient of their hospital system. She said the participant would need to share his/her EHR through the Care Evolution platform and she was wondering how this would affect their pairing status at their HPO.

 

I don’t believe this should have any bearing on the pairing status, but I was unsure about the general CE EHR Sharing process, so I wanted to reach out to you all to see if you happened to have a high-level explanation of the process that a participant who originates from the PTSC Portal would then share their EHR via the CE pathway. If you don’t I can reach out to CE directly, but I would think all EHR data would come through y’all at some point. 

 

I believe that the only thing that would affect anything would be if the ppt signed up via the CE Pathway, but this is not the case.

 

Thanks for your help!

 

Drew Ericson
Associate IT Business Analyst
Vanderbilt University Medical Center, Data and Research Center
2525 West End Ave | Nashville, TN 37203
Email: andrew.ericson@vumc.org
Website: allofus.nih.gov (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fallofus.nih.gov%2F&data=04%7C01%7Candrew.ericson%40vumc.org%7C4ed19401bd144c1c7cb108d8fdbeb174%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637538342741761599%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=LDSiPzUW%2FxDQbkJY8vwBtkthcL1h1Jy2iZVXMOJsMYY%3D&reserved=0)


 

 

 

 

 

 

 

From: DRC Support
Sent: Thursday, December 22, 2022 10:20 AM
To: Russo, Christine A. <CRUSSO@MGH.HARVARD.EDU>
Subject: RE: Inquiry About Non-Patient Participants Sharing EHR

 

Hi Christine, thank you for that thorough explanation of your question! That was very helpful in my understanding of the issue at hand.

 

So, my understanding of what lets the HPO locate the participant in PMT is the specific pathway through which the participant enters the program. For example, If the participant completes enrollment and consents (etc) through the PTSC’s Participant Portal, then you should be able to locate the participant on PMT. This is because PMT and the PTSC Portal are both managed by the PTSC.

 

If the participant completes enrollment via the Care Evolution Portal and signs consents (etc) through that platform, you would be unable to locate the participant on PMT, because CE and PMT are managed by different organizations.

 

So, I believe that, provided the participant originates via the PTSC platform (Which would be the standard HPO workflow), they should be visible in PMT. However, I am unsure about the EHR sharing portion specifically, so I will pass that portion of your question along to our EHR Ops team to get their input.

 

For any additional questions you may have about PMT, please reach out to the PTSC, as they are best equipped to address the specifics.

 

Regards,

 

Drew Ericson
Associate IT Business Analyst
Vanderbilt University Medical Center, Data and Research Center

2525 West End Ave | Nashville, TN 37203
Email: DRCSupport@vumc.org
Website: allofus.nih.gov (https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fallofus.nih.gov%2F&data=04%7C01%7Candrew.ericson%40vumc.org%7C4ed19401bd144c1c7cb108d8fdbeb174%7Cef57503014244ed8b83c12c533d879ab%7C0%7C0%7C637538342741761599%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C1000&sdata=LDSiPzUW%2FxDQbkJY8vwBtkthcL1h1Jy2iZVXMOJsMYY%3D&reserved=0)


 

 

From: Russo, Christine A. <CRUSSO@MGH.HARVARD.EDU>
Sent: Thursday, December 22, 2022 9:37 AM
To: DRC Support <drcsupport@vumc.org>
Subject: Inquiry About Non-Patient Participants Sharing EHR

 

Good Morning,

 

I was hoping to get some clarity about the process in which Participants who are not Patients with our New England HPO are able to share their EHR.

 

If a participant joins through the HPO websites (joinallofus.org or joinallofus.org/new-england), but they do not have EHR with our Mass General Brigham Institutions, when they consent to EHR and are taken through the CareEvolution path of sharing their records, will Our New England Team still be able to locate them in PMT / Pair them with our Organization and Sites?

 

I suppose there is some confusion on whether it is OK for to Participants to share EHR through CareEvolution and still be paired with us. I have received information about Participants joining through the Direct Volunteer sites (go.joinallofus.org), sharing EHR through CareEvolution, and then we cannot find the Pt in PMT or pair them (since they signed up as DV).

 

Could you confirm/clarify that Participants joining through the regular/our HPO websites can share their EHR through CareEvolution and still be paired with out HPO and Sites? (I understand if this would not be the case through DV website, as we have encountered it before).

 

Any information you can provide, or perhaps directing me to the correct contact with this question, would be greatly appreciated.

 

Thank you and best regards,

-Christine Russo

Operations Project Manager All of Us New England

Hi All of Us,

 

I support the ETL as data steward for the All of Us project.  But I’m starting to get questions from researchers about the All of Us “Researcher Workbench.”

 

Can someone please tell me:

 

1. How was training rolled out for the Researcher Workbench? 

 

1. As a data steward in charge of the quarterly E-T-L data submission, am I expected to have access and training on the Researcher Workbench? 

 

1. Who are the contact people at All of Us who can help field questions about the Researcher Workbench?

We are getting PI’s who are unsure if they are querying the correct concepts and are unhappy with how little information is in the Researcher Workbench, such as breast density for breast cancer.

 

I want to make sure there is buy-in to the Researcher Workbench.   Training and support will be critical.  I do not know who the Subject Matter Experts (SME) are.

 

Oliver Eng

Data Query Analyst

Clinical Research Data Service team (CRDS)

UW Madison School of Medicine and Public Health

description:
Hi Ryan,

 

I am looking at HealthPro API to see which participants we were not able to transfer with patient status “Yes”. I wanted to investigate into the status, but from the HealthPro API I can only see the variable “isEHRDataAvailable”. However, when looking at the variable, all participants are marked as “FALSE” or “UNSET” in our database. Is there a place on the dashboard(s) where we could find Patient Status “Yes” and EHR Transfer “No”? And if so, are there sets of variables that could reflected the totals on HealthPro?

 

Nripendra and Chun Yee – My apologies for not following up on this sooner as it has been long since our last conversation when looking into this. If you would like, please feel free to answer this as well.  

 

Thanks,

Christian

 

 

---

Christian Udu, MPH

He/Him

Biomedical Informatics Research Specialist, All of Us

Institute for Minority Health Research

University of Illinois Chicago.

E: cudu@uic.edu | O: 312-413-3568

description:
We are trying to determine which participants can be included in the DTR-C denominator, so we can target those participants for inclusion on the file and thereby boost our DTR-C rate.

I filtered all participants for EHR eligibility + DTR-C eligibility and got a count of 9866, which is significantly higher than the denominator of 9100 in the Data Transfer Assessment from 12/5/2022 for BSWH (see attached).

Granted, the dataset I used was pulled on 1/6/2023 – over a month after I sent the 2022 Q4 EHR files – but a difference of 766 seems too high to explain by pull date alone. So I’m wondering if you can help me track down where the discrepancy might be coming from.

The attached Word doc specifies the criteria I’m using to determine DTR-C eligibility. Text in blue refers to HealthPro Work Queue fields.
raw_subject: DTR-C eligibility criteria
subject: DTR-C eligibility criteria
